    <fr:title text="sheaf condition in terms of plus construction">sheaf condition in terms of plus construction</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  Given a presheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>, the morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P \to  P^+]]></fr:tex> to its <fr:link href="/forest/algm-001E/" title="plus construction" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/algm-001E/" display-uri="algm-001E" type="local">plus construction</fr:link> is a monomorphism iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/forest/algm-001F/" title="sheaf" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/algm-001F/" display-uri="algm-001F" type="local">separated</fr:link>, and it is an isomorphism iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/forest/algm-001F/" title="sheaf" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/algm-001F/" display-uri="algm-001F" type="local">sheaf</fr:link>.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
