            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Given a category <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> equipped with a <fr:link href="/forest/algm-0019/" title="coverage" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/algm-0019/" display-uri="algm-0019" type="local">coverage</fr:link>, we define a presheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P : \mathcal {C}^\textrm {op} \to  \mathsf {Set}]]></fr:tex> to be a <html:strong>sheaf</html:strong> if it satisfies the <html:strong>sheaf condition</html:strong>: for every cover of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, the map from sections of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:link href="/forest/algm-001D/" title="descent data of presheaves" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/algm-001D/" display-uri="algm-001D" type="local">descent data</fr:link> of the cover is a bijection. It is a <html:strong>separated presheaf</html:strong> if the map is an injection.
</html:p>
